SCOPE OF THIS SOFTWARE

ARCHITECT — Universal Coherence Engine is a real-time AI coherence
monitoring and correction layer for Claude API conversations. It includes:

  · TF-IDF + Jensen-Shannon Divergence coherence scoring (smoothed IDF,
    calibrated against working similarity post V1.5.38)
  · Kalman filter state estimation (GARCH-in-Mean coupled, V1.5.39)
  · GARCH(1,1) variance modeling with per-preset tuning
  · Stochastic Differential Equation simulation (OU + periodic forcing,
    jump-diffusion / Merton 1976, GARCH-in-Mean / Engle et al. 1987)
  · Signal detection: Shannon entropy, vocabulary growth rate, n-gram
    repetition, hedge density, response truncation, anchor distance,
    Kalman innovation autocorrelation, token efficiency ratio
  · Behavioral signal detection (7 proxies) and hallucination signal
    detection (5 proxies)
  · Pipe injection, RAG retrieval, harness escalation, EWMA trend
  · Framework mode disclosure: Hudson Framework (k=0.444) or Standard
    Mode (k=0.500), user-selectable at first run
  · Integrity Floor detection inspired by Trumble's Macro-Ratchet
    Framework (2026) and the hydrogen ionization floor concept
  · Advanced experimental features: MHT Study, Poole CA Simulator,
    CIR/Heston SDE models
  · TypeScript SDK for integration into external pipelines

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

RESEARCH & DEVELOPMENT NOTICE

This software is an experimental research and development tool. All outputs
including coherence scores, signal detections, variance states, Kalman
estimates, SDE bands, session health scores, and integrity breach events
are mathematical proxy indicators only. They do not constitute measurements,
assessments, diagnoses, or determinations of any kind.

THIS SOFTWARE MUST NOT BE USED — DIRECTLY OR INDIRECTLY — TO INFORM
MEDICAL, CLINICAL, LEGAL, FINANCIAL, SAFETY-CRITICAL, OR REGULATORY
DECISIONS. This prohibition applies regardless of deployment context.

The Hudson Framework constants (k=0.444, RESONANCE_ANCHOR=623.81 Hz)
are the default parameters of the Hudson-Perry Drift Law framework and
are disclosed to users at first run. Standard parameters (k=0.500) are
available as an alternative. Results generated under modified constants
operate outside the validated framework.

Advanced tab features (MHT Study, Poole CA Simulator, Integrity Floor,
CIR/Heston SDE models) are explicitly labeled experimental and require
user consent before activation. These features may include unvalidated
mathematical models and carry no empirical confirmation.

