THIRD-PARTY THEORETICAL REFERENCES

This software incorporates concepts from or is informed by the following
independent works, used for theoretical framing only:

  · Engle, R.F., Lilien, D.M., & Robins, R.P. (1987). Estimating time
    varying risk premia in the term structure: The ARCH-M model.
    Econometrica, 55(2), 391-407. [GARCH-in-Mean coupling]

  · Merton, R.C. (1976). Option pricing when underlying stock returns are
    discontinuous. Journal of Financial Economics, 3(1-2), 125-144.
    [Jump-diffusion model]

  · Box, G.E.P. & Jenkins, G.M. (1970). Time Series Analysis: Forecasting
    and Control. [Kalman innovation whiteness check]

  · Kim, Kojaku, Ahn et al. (2026). Embedding Disruptiveness Measure.
    Science Advances, April 2026. [45-degree angular invariant parallel]

  · Trumble, R.T. (2026). The Macro-Ratchet Framework: Coherent Ordering
    Dynamics and Universal Predictive Algebra. Zenodo.
    [Integrity Floor / hydrogen ionization floor concept]

These references informed conceptual development. Inclusion does not imply
endorsement by or affiliation with any referenced author or institution.

